1023/* Khronos platform-specific types and definitions.
1024 *
1025 * The master copy of khrplatform.h is maintained in the Khronos EGL
1026 * Registry repository at https://github.com/KhronosGroup/EGL-Registry
1027 * The last semantic modification to khrplatform.h was at commit ID:
1028 * 67a3e0864c2d75ea5287b9f3d2eb74a745936692
1029 *
1030 * Adopters may modify this file to suit their platform. Adopters are
1031 * encouraged to submit platform specific modifications to the Khronos
1032 * group so that they can be included in future versions of this file.
1033 * Please submit changes by filing pull requests or issues on
1034 * the EGL Registry repository linked above.
1035 *
1036 *
1037 * See the Implementer's Guidelines for information about where this file
1038 * should be located on your system and for more details of its use:
1039 * http://www.khronos.org/registry/implementers_guide.pdf
1040 *
1041 * This file should be included as
1042 * #include <KHR/khrplatform.h>
1043 * by Khronos client API header files that use its types and defines.
1044 *
1045 * The types in khrplatform.h should only be used to define API-specific types.
1046 *
1047 * Types defined in khrplatform.h:
1048 * khronos_int8_t signed 8 bit
1049 * khronos_uint8_t unsigned 8 bit
1050 * khronos_int16_t signed 16 bit
1051 * khronos_uint16_t unsigned 16 bit
1052 * khronos_int32_t signed 32 bit
1053 * khronos_uint32_t unsigned 32 bit
1054 * khronos_int64_t signed 64 bit
1055 * khronos_uint64_t unsigned 64 bit
1056 * khronos_intptr_t signed same number of bits as a pointer
1057 * khronos_uintptr_t unsigned same number of bits as a pointer
1058 * khronos_ssize_t signed size
1059 * khronos_usize_t unsigned size
1060 * khronos_float_t signed 32 bit floating point
1061 * khronos_time_ns_t unsigned 64 bit time in nanoseconds
1062 * khronos_utime_nanoseconds_t unsigned time interval or absolute time in
1063 * nanoseconds
1064 * khronos_stime_nanoseconds_t signed time interval in nanoseconds
1065 * khronos_boolean_enum_t enumerated boolean type. This should
1066 * only be used as a base type when a client API's boolean type is
1067 * an enum. Client APIs which use an integer or other type for
1068 * booleans cannot use this as the base type for their boolean.
1069 *
1070 * Tokens defined in khrplatform.h:
1071 *
1072 * KHRONOS_FALSE, KHRONOS_TRUE Enumerated boolean false/true values.
1073 *
1074 * KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 is 1 if 64 bit integers are supported; otherwise 0.
1075 * KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT is 1 if floats are supported; otherwise 0.
1076 *
1077 * Calling convention macros defined in this file:
1078 * KHRONOS_APICALL
1079 * KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR
1080 * KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES
1081 *
1082 * These may be used in function prototypes as:
1083 *
1084 * KHRONOS_APICALL void KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR funcname(
1085 * int arg1,
1086 * int arg2) KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES;
1087 */
1088
1089#if defined(__SCITECH_SNAP__) && !defined(KHRONOS_STATIC)
1090# define KHRONOS_STATIC 1
1091#endif
1092
1093/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1094 * Definition of KHRONOS_APICALL
1095 *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1096 * This precedes the return type of the function in the function prototype.
1097 */
1098#if defined(KHRONOS_STATIC)
1099 /* If the preprocessor constant KHRONOS_STATIC is defined, make the
1100 * header compatible with static linking. */
1101# define KHRONOS_APICALL
1102#elif defined(_WIN32)
1103# define KHRONOS_APICALL __declspec(dllimport)
1104#elif defined (__SYMBIAN32__)
1105# define KHRONOS_APICALL IMPORT_C
1106#elif defined(__ANDROID__)
1107# define KHRONOS_APICALL __attribute__((visibility("default")))
1108#else
1109# define KHRONOS_APICALL
1110#endif
1111
1112/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1113 * Definition of KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR
1114 *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1115 * This follows the return type of the function and precedes the function
1116 * name in the function prototype.
1117 */
1118#if defined(_WIN32) && !defined(_WIN32_WCE) && !defined(__SCITECH_SNAP__)
1119 /* Win32 but not WinCE */
1120# define KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR __stdcall
1121#else
1122# define KHRONOS_GLAD_API_PTR
1123#endif
1124
1125/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1126 * Definition of KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES
1127 *-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1128 * This follows the closing parenthesis of the function prototype arguments.
1129 */
1130#if defined (__ARMCC_2__)
1131#define KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES __softfp
1132#else
1133#define KHRONOS_APIATTRIBUTES
1134#endif
1135
1136/*-------------------------------------------------------------------------
1137 * basic type definitions
1138 *-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1139#if (defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && __STDC_VERSION__ >= 199901L) || defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__SCO__) || defined(__USLC__)
1140
1141
1142/*
1143 * Using <stdint.h>
1144 */
1145#include <stdint.h>
1146typedef int32_t khronos_int32_t;
1147typedef uint32_t khronos_uint32_t;
1148typedef int64_t khronos_int64_t;
1149typedef uint64_t khronos_uint64_t;
1150#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 1
1151#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT 1
1152/*
1153 * To support platform where unsigned long cannot be used interchangeably with
1154 * inptr_t (e.g. CHERI-extended ISAs), we can use the stdint.h intptr_t.
1155 * Ideally, we could just use (u)intptr_t everywhere, but this could result in
1156 * ABI breakage if khronos_uintptr_t is changed from unsigned long to
1157 * unsigned long long or similar (this results in different C++ name mangling).
1158 * To avoid changes for existing platforms, we restrict usage of intptr_t to
1159 * platforms where the size of a pointer is larger than the size of long.
1160 */
1161#if defined(__SIZEOF_LONG__) && defined(__SIZEOF_POINTER__)
1162#if __SIZEOF_POINTER__ > __SIZEOF_LONG__
1163#define KHRONOS_USE_INTPTR_T
1164#endif
1165#endif
1166
1167#elif defined(__VMS ) || defined(__sgi)
1168
1169/*
1170 * Using <inttypes.h>
1171 */
1172#include <inttypes.h>
1173typedef int32_t khronos_int32_t;
1174typedef uint32_t khronos_uint32_t;
1175typedef int64_t khronos_int64_t;
1176typedef uint64_t khronos_uint64_t;
1177#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 1
1178#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT 1
1179
1180#elif defined(_WIN32) && !defined(__SCITECH_SNAP__)
1181
1182/*
1183 * Win32
1184 */
1185typedef __int32 khronos_int32_t;
1186typedef unsigned __int32 khronos_uint32_t;
1187typedef __int64 khronos_int64_t;
1188typedef unsigned __int64 khronos_uint64_t;
1189#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 1
1190#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT 1
1191
1192#elif defined(__sun__) || defined(__digital__)
1193
1194/*
1195 * Sun or Digital
1196 */
1197typedef int khronos_int32_t;
1198typedef unsigned int khronos_uint32_t;
1199#if defined(__arch64__) || defined(_LP64)
1200typedef long int khronos_int64_t;
1201typedef unsigned long int khronos_uint64_t;
1202#else
1203typedef long long int khronos_int64_t;
1204typedef unsigned long long int khronos_uint64_t;
1205#endif /* __arch64__ */
1206#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 1
1207#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT 1
1208
1209#elif 0
1210
1211/*
1212 * Hypothetical platform with no float or int64 support
1213 */
1214typedef int khronos_int32_t;
1215typedef unsigned int khronos_uint32_t;
1216#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 0
1217#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT 0
1218
1219#else
1220
1221/*
1222 * Generic fallback
1223 */
1224#include <stdint.h>
1225typedef int32_t khronos_int32_t;
1226typedef uint32_t khronos_uint32_t;
1227typedef int64_t khronos_int64_t;
1228typedef uint64_t khronos_uint64_t;
1229#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64 1
1230#define KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT 1
1231
1232#endif

1235/*
1236 * Types that are (so far) the same on all platforms
1237 */
1238typedef signed char khronos_int8_t;
1239typedef unsigned char khronos_uint8_t;
1240typedef signed short int khronos_int16_t;
1241typedef unsigned short int khronos_uint16_t;
1242
1243/*
1244 * Types that differ between LLP64 and LP64 architectures - in LLP64,
1245 * pointers are 64 bits, but 'long' is still 32 bits. Win64 appears
1246 * to be the only LLP64 architecture in current use.
1247 */
1248#ifdef KHRONOS_USE_INTPTR_T
1249typedef intptr_t khronos_intptr_t;
1250typedef uintptr_t khronos_uintptr_t;
1251#elif defined(_WIN64)
1252typedef signed long long int khronos_intptr_t;
1253typedef unsigned long long int khronos_uintptr_t;
1254#else
1255typedef signed long int khronos_intptr_t;
1256typedef unsigned long int khronos_uintptr_t;
1257#endif
1258
1259#if defined(_WIN64)
1260typedef signed long long int khronos_ssize_t;
1261typedef unsigned long long int khronos_usize_t;
1262#else
1263typedef signed long int khronos_ssize_t;
1264typedef unsigned long int khronos_usize_t;
1265#endif
1266
1267#if KHRONOS_SUPPORT_FLOAT
1268/*
1269 * Float type
1270 */
1271typedef float khronos_float_t;
1272#endif
1273
1274#if KHRONOS_SUPPORT_INT64
1275/* Time types
1276 *
1277 * These types can be used to represent a time interval in nanoseconds or
1278 * an absolute Unadjusted System Time. Unadjusted System Time is the number
1279 * of nanoseconds since some arbitrary system event (e.g. since the last
1280 * time the system booted). The Unadjusted System Time is an unsigned
1281 * 64 bit value that wraps back to 0 every 584 years. Time intervals
1282 * may be either signed or unsigned.
1283 */
1284typedef khronos_uint64_t khronos_utime_nanoseconds_t;
1285typedef khronos_int64_t khronos_stime_nanoseconds_t;
1286#endif
1287
1288/*
1289 * Dummy value used to pad enum types to 32 bits.
1290 */
1291#ifndef KHRONOS_MAX_ENUM
1292#define KHRONOS_MAX_ENUM 0x7FFFFFFF
1293#endif
1294
1295/*
1296 * Enumerated boolean type
1297 *
1298 * Values other than zero should be considered to be true. Therefore
1299 * comparisons should not be made against KHRONOS_TRUE.
1300 */
1301typedef enum {
1302 KHRONOS_FALSE = 0,
1303 KHRONOS_TRUE = 1,
1304 KHRONOS_BOOLEAN_ENUM_FORCE_SIZE = KHRONOS_MAX_ENUM
1305} khronos_boolean_enum_t;
1306
1307#endif /* __khrplatform_h_ */

3222#if defined(GL_ES_VERSION_3_0) || defined(GL_VERSION_3_0)

3224#else
3225#define GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION 0
3226#endif
3227
3228static int glad_gl_get_extensions( int version, const char **out_exts, unsigned int *out_num_exts_i, char ***out_exts_i) {
3229#if GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION
3230 if(GLAD_VERSION_MAJOR(version) < 3) {
3231#else
3232 (void) version;
3233 (void) out_num_exts_i;
3234 (void) out_exts_i;
3235#endif
3236 if (glad_glGetString == NULL) {
3237 return 0;
3238 }
3239 *out_exts = (const char *)glad_glGetString(GL_EXTENSIONS);
3240#if GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION
3241 } else {
3242 unsigned int index = 0;
3243 unsigned int num_exts_i = 0;
3244 char **exts_i = NULL;
3245 if (glad_glGetStringi == NULL || glad_glGetIntegerv == NULL) {
3246 return 0;
3247 }
3248 glad_glGetIntegerv(GL_NUM_EXTENSIONS, (int*) &num_exts_i);
3249 if (num_exts_i > 0) {
3250 exts_i = (char **) malloc(num_exts_i * (sizeof *exts_i));
3251 }
3252 if (exts_i == NULL) {
3253 return 0;
3254 }
3255 for(index = 0; index < num_exts_i; index++) {
3256 const char *gl_str_tmp = (const char*) glad_glGetStringi(GL_EXTENSIONS, index);
3257 size_t len = strlen(gl_str_tmp) + 1;
3258
3259 char *local_str = (char*) malloc(len * sizeof(char));
3260 if(local_str != NULL) {
3261 memcpy(local_str, gl_str_tmp, len * sizeof(char));
3262 }
3263
3264 exts_i[index] = local_str;
3265 }
3266
3267 *out_num_exts_i = num_exts_i;
3268 *out_exts_i = exts_i;
3269 }
3270#endif
3271 return 1;
3272}
3273static void glad_gl_free_extensions(char **exts_i, unsigned int num_exts_i) {
3274 if (exts_i != NULL) {
3275 unsigned int index;
3276 for(index = 0; index < num_exts_i; index++) {
3277 free((void *) (exts_i[index]));
3278 }
3279 free((void *)exts_i);
3280 exts_i = NULL;
3281 }
3282}
3283static int glad_gl_has_extension(int version, const char *exts, unsigned int num_exts_i, char **exts_i, const char *ext) {
3284 if(GLAD_VERSION_MAJOR(version) < 3 || !GLAD_GL_IS_SOME_NEW_VERSION) {
3285 const char *extensions;
3286 const char *loc;
3287 const char *terminator;
3288 extensions = exts;
3289 if(extensions == NULL || ext == NULL) {
3290 return 0;
3291 }
3292 while(1) {
3293 loc = strstr(extensions, ext);
3294 if(loc == NULL) {
3295 return 0;
3296 }
3297 terminator = loc + strlen(ext);
3298 if((loc == extensions || *(loc - 1) == ' ') &&
3299 (*terminator == ' ' || *terminator == '\0')) {
3300 return 1;
3301 }
3302 extensions = terminator;
3303 }
3304 } else {
3305 unsigned int index;
3306 for(index = 0; index < num_exts_i; index++) {
3307 const char *e = exts_i[index];
3308 if(strcmp(e, ext) == 0) {
3309 return 1;
3310 }
3311 }
3312 }
3313 return 0;
3314}

3316static GLADapiproc glad_gl_get_proc_from_userptr(void *userptr, const char* name) {
3317 return (GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (GLADapiproc (*)(const char *name)) userptr)(name);
3318}
3319
3320static int glad_gl_find_extensions_gl( int version) {
3321 const char *exts = NULL;
3322 unsigned int num_exts_i = 0;
3323 char **exts_i = NULL;
3324 if (!glad_gl_get_extensions(version, &exts, &num_exts_i, &exts_i)) return 0;
3325
3326 (void) glad_gl_has_extension;
3327
3328 glad_gl_free_extensions(exts_i, num_exts_i);
3329
3330 return 1;
3331}
3332
3333static int glad_gl_find_core_gl(void) {
3334 int i;
3335 const char* version;
3336 const char* prefixes[] = {
3337 "OpenGL ES-CM ",
3338 "OpenGL ES-CL ",
3339 "OpenGL ES ",
3340 "OpenGL SC ",
3341 NULL
3342 };
3343 int major = 0;
3344 int minor = 0;
3345 version = (const char*) glad_glGetString(GL_VERSION);
3346 if (!version) return 0;
3347 for (i = 0; prefixes[i]; i++) {
3348 const size_t length = strlen(prefixes[i]);
3349 if (strncmp(version, prefixes[i], length) == 0) {
3350 version += length;
3351 break;
3352 }
3353 }
3354
3355 GLAD_IMPL_UTIL_SSCANF(version, "%d.%d", &major, &minor);
3356
3357 GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_0 = (major == 1 && minor >= 0) || major > 1;
3358 GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_1 = (major == 1 && minor >= 1) || major > 1;
3359 GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_2 = (major == 1 && minor >= 2) || major > 1;
3360 GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_3 = (major == 1 && minor >= 3) || major > 1;
3361 GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_4 = (major == 1 && minor >= 4) || major > 1;
3362 GLAD_GL_VERSION_1_5 = (major == 1 && minor >= 5) || major > 1;
3363 GLAD_GL_VERSION_2_0 = (major == 2 && minor >= 0) || major > 2;
3364 GLAD_GL_VERSION_2_1 = (major == 2 && minor >= 1) || major > 2;
3365 GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_0 = (major == 3 && minor >= 0) || major > 3;
3366 GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_1 = (major == 3 && minor >= 1) || major > 3;
3367 GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_2 = (major == 3 && minor >= 2) || major > 3;
3368 GLAD_GL_VERSION_3_3 = (major == 3 && minor >= 3) || major > 3;
3369
3370 return GLAD_MAKE_VERSION(major, minor);
3371}
3372
3373int gladLoadGLUserPtr( GLADuserptrloadfunc load, void *userptr) {
3374 int version;
3375
3376 glad_glGetString = (PFNGLGETSTRINGPROC) load(userptr, "glGetString");
3377 if(glad_glGetString == NULL) return 0;
3378 if(glad_glGetString(GL_VERSION) == NULL) return 0;
3379 version = glad_gl_find_core_gl();
3380
3381 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_1_0(load, userptr);
3382 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_1_1(load, userptr);
3383 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_1_2(load, userptr);
3384 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_1_3(load, userptr);
3385 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_1_4(load, userptr);
3386 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_1_5(load, userptr);
3387 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_2_0(load, userptr);
3388 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_2_1(load, userptr);
3389 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_3_0(load, userptr);
3390 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_3_1(load, userptr);
3391 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_3_2(load, userptr);
3392 glad_gl_load_GL_VERSION_3_3(load, userptr);
3393
3394 if (!glad_gl_find_extensions_gl(version)) return 0;
3395
3396
3397
3398 return version;
3399}

3425static void* glad_get_dlopen_handle(const char *lib_names[], int length) {
3426 void *handle = NULL;
3427 int i;
3428
3429 for (i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
3430#if GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
3431 #if GLAD_PLATFORM_UWP
3432 size_t buffer_size = (strlen(lib_names[i]) + 1) * sizeof(WCHAR);
3433 LPWSTR buffer = (LPWSTR) malloc(buffer_size);
3434 if (buffer != NULL) {
3435 int ret = MultiByteToWideChar(CP_ACP, 0, lib_names[i], -1, buffer, buffer_size);
3436 if (ret != 0) {
3437 handle = (void*) LoadPackagedLibrary(buffer, 0);
3438 }
3439 free((void*) buffer);
3440 }
3441 #else
3442 handle = (void*) LoadLibraryA(lib_names[i]);
3443 #endif
3444#else
3445 handle = dlopen(lib_names[i], RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_LOCAL);
3446#endif
3447 if (handle != NULL) {
3448 return handle;
3449 }
3450 }
3451
3452 return NULL;
3453}
3454
3455static void glad_close_dlopen_handle(void* handle) {
3456 if (handle != NULL) {
3457#if GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
3458 FreeLibrary((HMODULE) handle);
3459#else
3460 dlclose(handle);
3461#endif
3462 }
3463}
3464
3465static GLADapiproc glad_dlsym_handle(void* handle, const char *name) {
3466 if (handle == NULL) {
3467 return NULL;
3468 }
3469
3470#if GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
3471 return (GLADapiproc) GetProcAddress((HMODULE) handle, name);
3472#else
3473 return GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (GLADapiproc) dlsym(handle, name);
3474#endif
3475}

3479typedef void* (GLAD_API_PTR *GLADglprocaddrfunc)(const char*);
3480struct _glad_gl_userptr {
3481 void *handle;
3482 GLADglprocaddrfunc gl_get_proc_address_ptr;
3483};
3484
3485static GLADapiproc glad_gl_get_proc(void *vuserptr, const char *name) {
3486 struct _glad_gl_userptr userptr = *(struct _glad_gl_userptr*) vuserptr;
3487 GLADapiproc result = NULL;
3488
3489 if(userptr.gl_get_proc_address_ptr != NULL) {
3490 result = GLAD_GNUC_EXTENSION (GLADapiproc) userptr.gl_get_proc_address_ptr(name);
3491 }
3492 if(result == NULL) {
3493 result = glad_dlsym_handle(userptr.handle, name);
3494 }
3495
3496 return result;
3497}

3499static void* _gl_handle = NULL;
3500
3501static void* glad_gl_dlopen_handle(void) {
3502#if GLAD_PLATFORM_APPLE
3503 static const char *NAMES[] = {
3504 "../Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/OpenGL",
3505 "/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/OpenGL",
3506 "/System/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/OpenGL",
3507 "/System/Library/Frameworks/OpenGL.framework/Versions/Current/OpenGL"
3508 };
3509#elif GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
3510 static const char *NAMES[] = {"opengl32.dll"};
3511#else
3512 static const char *NAMES[] = {
3513 #if defined(__CYGWIN__)
3514 "libGL-1.so",
3515 #endif
3516 "libGL.so.1",
3517 "libGL.so"
3518 };
3519#endif
3520
3521 if (_gl_handle == NULL) {
3522 _gl_handle = glad_get_dlopen_handle(NAMES, sizeof(NAMES) / sizeof(NAMES[0]));
3523 }
3524
3525 return _gl_handle;
3526}
3527
3528static struct _glad_gl_userptr glad_gl_build_userptr(void *handle) {
3529 struct _glad_gl_userptr userptr;
3530
3531 userptr.handle = handle;
3532#if GLAD_PLATFORM_APPLE || defined(__HAIKU__)
3533 userptr.gl_get_proc_address_ptr = NULL;
3534#elif GLAD_PLATFORM_WIN32
3535 userptr.gl_get_proc_address_ptr =
3536 (GLADglprocaddrfunc) glad_dlsym_handle(handle, "wglGetProcAddress");
3537#else
3538 userptr.gl_get_proc_address_ptr =
3539 (GLADglprocaddrfunc) glad_dlsym_handle(handle, "glXGetProcAddressARB");
3540#endif
3541
3542 return userptr;
3543}
3544
3545int gladLoaderLoadGL(void) {
3546 int version = 0;
3547 void *handle;
3548 int did_load = 0;
3549 struct _glad_gl_userptr userptr;
3550
3551 did_load = _gl_handle == NULL;
3552 handle = glad_gl_dlopen_handle();
3553 if (handle) {
3554 userptr = glad_gl_build_userptr(handle);
3555
3556 version = gladLoadGLUserPtr(glad_gl_get_proc, &userptr);
3557
3558 if (did_load) {
3559 gladLoaderUnloadGL();
3560 }
3561 }
3562
3563 return version;
3564}

3568void gladLoaderUnloadGL(void) {
3569 if (_gl_handle != NULL) {
3570 glad_close_dlopen_handle(_gl_handle);
3571 _gl_handle = NULL;
3572 }
3573}
